			<div class="page-header">
  				<h1 style="margin-top:50px">San Francisco Homeless Challenge</h1>
			</div>
			<p> We chose this project because we believe that the homeless population in San Francisco is 
			growing and we wanted to try a long-term approach to solving this problem. Instead of providing immediate
			resources, we wanted to provide resources for homeless people to get jobs and become self-sufficient.</p>
			<p>There are <strong style= "color:#00A9DE">6,686</strong> in San Francisco without a place to live. San Francisco has 
			the <strong style= "color:#00A9DE">second</strong> largest homeless population in the United States. <strong style= "color:#00A9DE">89%</strong>
			of homeless people are unemployed. The most common reason reported for homelessness was job loss. <strong style= "color:#00A9DE">48%
			</strong>reported not being able to afford rent as their main obstacle to obtaining permanent housing
			and <strong style= "color:#00A9DE">28%</strong> reported a lack of job or income as their obstacle.
			<strong style= "color:#00A9DE"> 34%
			</strong> of the homeless population reported they had been homeless <strong style= "color:#00A9DE">4</strong> or more times, and 
			<strong style= "color:#00A9DE">25%</strong> of respondents reported they had experienced homelessness <strong style= "color:#00A9DE">
			4</strong> or more times in the past year.</p>
			
			
